products.description: The Aquaria AI as a Service offers an Image Classification CNN model that is capable of accurately identifying and classifying four different fish species commonly found in the Philippines: Perch, Tarpon, Tilapia, and Catfish. The model has been trained on a large dataset of high-quality synthetic images of these fish species, and it uses advanced machine learning algorithms to recognize the unique features and characteristics of each species. With its high level of accuracy and reliability, the Aquaria Image Classification CNN model is a valuable tool for fisheries management, conservation efforts, and scientific research.

products.description: Aquaria AI as a Service offers an Image Classification CNN model that can accurately identify and classify various aquatic plants commonly found in marine ecosystems. This model has been trained on a large dataset of high-quality images of different aquatic plant species, utilizing advanced machine learning algorithms to recognize the unique features and characteristics of each species. The Aquaria Image Classification CNN model provides accurate and reliable results, making it an essential tool for researchers, environmentalists, and aquatic biologists to identify and monitor the diversity and abundance of aquatic plant species in marine ecosystems.
